# FinTrack AI — Server / DB Rules

## 1. Always filter by userId

Every query on user-owned data must include `userId` in the WHERE clause.

```typescript
// ✅
.where(and(eq(transactions.userId, userId), eq(transactions.isDeleted, false)))

// ❌ Missing userId — exposes other users' data
.where(eq(transactions.isDeleted, false))
```

## 2. Soft delete only — never hard delete

```typescript
// ✅
await db.update(transactions).set({ isDeleted: true }).where(...)

// ❌
await db.delete(transactions).where(...)
```

## 3. Dates are varchar(10) strings — never Date objects

```typescript
// ✅
const transactionDate = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]; // "2026-03-24"

// ❌ — causes Drizzle type error
const transactionDate = new Date();
```

## 4. Decimal columns return as strings — Number() before math

```typescript
// ✅
const pct = Number(budget.pctUsed) * 100;

// ❌ — produces NaN
const pct = budget.pctUsed * 100;
```

## 5. Recalc budgets after every expense transaction mutation

```typescript
// In db.ts — after insert, update, or soft-delete of an expense transaction:
await recalcBudgetSpent(categoryId);
```

## 6. Market API — do NOT use api.metals.live (ISSUE-002)

Use Yahoo Finance `GC=F` / `SI=F` or SJC API instead. `api.metals.live` is blocked.

## 7. Source of truth for schema

`drizzle/schema.ts` is the single source of truth for all tables. Never hand-write SQL; always use Drizzle query builder.
